<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="70" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1863,2032]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1899,1924]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small body size (
<quantity box="[525,694,1900,1924]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.425" metricValueMax="1.55" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="1.425" valueMax="1.55" valueMin="1.3">1.30–1.55 mm</quantity>
), elongate, reddish-brown, shiny. Rostrum dorsally finely punctuate, apex smooth and shiny. Pronotum with dense, round punctures. Protibia with external teeth. Elytra with second and third intervals raised above first and second striae, each with 
<number box="[918,1001,1972,1996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8 to 10</number>
round punctures, not always aligned, between the base and declivity.
</paragraph>
